s\n why I said that *lightness of conditioning* is the m=\r\nost important thing. One with dense conditioning will find SOME way to fail=\r\n even if a great guru or god are ready to help. =C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 * =C2=\r\n=A0 Now, the question is: How do we reduce our conditioning? Unfortunately,=\r\n there is no single magic bullet. Thinking of a god, mantras, bhajans, japa=\r\nm, homam etc can help, but they need to be augmented by regular introspecti=\r\non and self-improvement. =C2=A0 Taking mind away from its current pre-occup=\r\nations (e.g. &quot;I am smart&quot;, &quot;I am doing good sadhana&quot;, &quot;I am mad at X&quot;, &quot;I d=\r\nid not get what I deserve in Y&quot;, &quot;I am better than X&quot;, &quot;I must have Y at an=\r\ny cost&quot; etc etc) is key to eventually overcoming conditioning, for these th=\r\noughts keep *reinforcing* the conditioning! =C2=A0 To reduce the regular pr=\r\ne-occupations of mind, different imagery/visualization may work better for =\r\nsome people. =C2=A0 One approach is to contemplate god whenever possible, i=\r\nn the middle of\n any activity. You can imagine a being in your mind, either=\r\n as an ideal/able person or as a principle/ideal/ability that exists in man=\r\ny beings, that is so perfect and fascinating for the mind to contemplate th=\r\nat it does not care about other objects around that are making shadripus an=\r\nd ashtapashas work on the mind. Whenever mind is about to entertain its reg=\r\nular debilitating pre-occupations, one can try to contemplate god instead. =\r\n=C2=A0 Mind is a wild animal. As Pi says in the movie &quot;Life of Pi&quot; about th=\r\ne tiger on the boat, wild animals can&#39;t be transformed or domesticated, but=\r\n they can be trained into some habits! =C2=A0 Whenever one is enjoying a se=\r\nnsual pleasure, if one thinks &quot;the omnipresent God is enjoying this thru th=\r\nis instrument&quot; and starts contemplating the qualities of that god instead o=\r\nf thinking too much about limited sense objects, one is better placed to re=\r\nduce the damage done by shadripus. Whenever one is angry at someone for wha=\r\nt they did, if\n one thinks &quot;the omnipresent God is giving me the fruits of =\r\nmy karmas thru that instrument&quot; and starts contemplating the qualities of t=\r\nhat god instead of being angry at someone, one is better placed to reduce t=\r\nhe damage done by shadripus. And so on. =C2=A0 In the beginning, even conte=\r\nmplation of god becomes laced with ego. Every now and then, the activity en=\r\nds up becoming about oneself rather than about god (&quot;*I* am doing this nice=\r\n bhajan&quot;, &quot;*I* am doing this nice homam&quot;, &quot;I think *I* am making progress t=\r\nhrough this&quot;). With effort and perseverance, one can avoid making it about =\r\noneself and keep it centered on the supreme power that runs the show. Just =\r\nas it takes a long time to train a wild animal, it takes a long time to tra=\r\nin mind! =C2=A0 Try to develop devotion and surrender. Based on all that yo=\r\nu read and heard, develop of a concept/principle of god that is so superb a=\r\nnd fascinarting. Visualize/contemplate that concept as frequently as possib=\r\nle, especially\n when meditating. When mind veers off into other things, gen=\r\ntly steer it back. Don&#39;t spend too much time dissecting what mind is doing =\r\nand why. Just put it back gently into contemplating god. Try to make it abo=\r\nut god rather than about yourself. =C2=A0 The main drawback of the sadhana =\r\nof most people is that they make it about themselves at some level or the o=\r\nther. Though that is unavoidable, try to break free from it. =C2=A0 *=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0 * =C2=A0 Finally, one can try to overcome the limited sense of self =\r\nand engage in selfless actions that benefit a larger set of people than one=\r\nself. What stops us from truly loving god is our deep and sub-conscious lov=\r\ne for *ourselves* (i.e. our *limited* notion of self that drives the curren=\r\nt body-mind complex). One way to overcome that is to selflessly love others=\r\n. After all, other people around us are as much replicas of god as we are. =\r\nIf we cannot empathize with them, love them and give them unconditionally,\n=\r\n how can we ever hope to transcend the limited sense of Self and truly love=\r\n omnipresent God? =C2=A0 \n&gt;&gt;Best regards, Narasimha -------- Astrology & Sp=\r\nirituality Resources: http://www.vedicastrologer.org/\n&gt;&gt;--------\n&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;=\r\n&gt;From: Leela Sastry &lt;leela.sastry@...&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;To: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogrou=\r\nps.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;&gt;&gt;Sent: Thursday, February 28, 201=\r\n3 10:35 PM\n&gt;&gt;&gt;Subject: Re: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Kundalini syndrome\n&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0 \n&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0Dear Friends ,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0All psychosomatic or schizophrenic ca=\r\nses are not defined as=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 wrongly=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 experime=\r\nnted=C2=A0=C2=A0kundalini=C2=A0=C2=A0 experiences . But some could be=C2=A0=\r\n , because=C2=A0 I personally know two to three cases .A very=C2=A0=C2=A0in=\r\ntelligent boy who did his masters in BITs -Pilani did some=C2=A0 experiment=\r\ning with that after going through=C2=A0 the material=C2=A0about kundalini i=\r\nn the net . He ended=C2=A0 up=C2=A0an incurable case of=C2=A0 some severe p=\r\nsychological disorder . Same=C2=A0 way a lady who did much sadhana of Srira=\r\nma ended up as a case of the same=C2=A0 or similar disorder after some time=\r\n . It is not confirm the point nor=C2=A0 to discourage or encourage the sad=\r\nhana . What is explained=C2=A0 aboutkundalini and the attitude of detachmen=\r\nt is perfectly correct . But to reach that state is very difficult for all =\r\n=C2=A0and=C2=A0 