 for out of body experiences due to Kundalini rise), is it an=\r\n achievement? In fact, it comes with risks. The former approach is safer an=\r\nd one loses nothing in it. Similarly, one can progress towards complete Sel=\r\nf-realization without any out of body experiences. These are not my word&#39;s,=\r\n but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s words to Lord Rama.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Secondly, one =\r\ndoes not get something without wanting it and putting sufficient effort tow=\r\nards it. One may have deeply desired a Kundalini rise in a previous life an=\r\nd may have put enough effort. As a result, one may be getting it now. But o=\r\nne may be unprepared (and ironically may not even want it!) when it comes i=\r\nn this life.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;As you do sadhana, try not to fancy too many sp=\r\necific desires. Nature has a delay mechanism in granting your desires (beca=\r\nuse of constraints on what\n Nature can give you right now, arising from YOU=\r\nR OWN previous actions). So Nature sometimes gives you what you want LATE, =\r\nwhen you no longer want it or want something else. For example, one may pra=\r\ny for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and be born as a rich but very sick man=\r\n in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life for health=\r\n. In the life after that, one may be very healthy, but not have any knowled=\r\nge or money. In another case, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film=\r\n. One may be reborn as a tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not r=\r\neally enjoy that experience. Basically, people keep going in circles throug=\r\nh various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n=\r\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an out of body =\r\nexperience given by a rising Kundalini and one&#39;s\n previous karmas constrain=\r\n one from having it in THIS life, one may be born in next life with this sp=\r\necific desire destined to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind =\r\nit).\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not ne=\r\ncessarily scary or painful, if one is well-prepared in terms of attitude an=\r\nd detachment.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I=\r\n went to free it and it panicked so badly and started to shake violently. I=\r\n went to save it from a certain slow death and it was scared that I would k=\r\nill it!\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap c=\r\nalled this body-mind complex and scared of being rescued from a certain slo=\r\nw death!\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;If our ideas about who we are (viz this current bod=\r\ny-mind complex) are incorrect and if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastra=\r\ns say, won&#39;t a complete realization of that at some\n stage involve stepping=\r\n out of this body-mind complex, without being scared?\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Kundalini rise after most undesirable conditioni=\r\nng is overcome, is far better than Kundalini rise forced when some really u=\r\nndesirable conditioning is still left in one&#39;s system.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;When =\r\none transcends one problematic notion about who one is and what one needs, =\r\nanother notion that lay buried deeper in consciousness may spring to the su=\r\nrface and torment one. If one overcomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there m=\r\nay be another notion in one&#39;s body-mind complex that one&#39;s awareness clings=\r\n on to (e.g. a great doctor, a great leader, a great scholar, a great saint=\r\n etc). As an extreme example, if one person had a hidden deep desire to be =\r\na great soul who rescues the world, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated=\r\n X or Y who will rescue the world now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kund=\r\nalini!) deeply clings to any such notion, it can cause havoc. The person ma=\r\ny show some signs of progress and yet remain in ignorance and get stuck bad=\r\nly.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;An awakened Kundalini in a system with undesirable condi=\r\ntioning may accentuate one&#39;s weaknesses and wrong notions heavily and cause=\r\n serious psychiatric and spiritual problems.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 =\r\n*\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;The best approach I recommend is to NOT think in terms of =\r\nKundalini and its rise. Just do sadhana, overcome your weaknesses and impro=\r\nve your detachment over time. Again, I want to emphasize that detachment is=\r\n not disgust or distaste for life/things/people around you. Disgust is the =\r\nother side of coin of attachment. It is a negative attachment. =C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;D=\r\non&#39;t worry about whether your Kundalini rises or not. Worry about whether y=\r\nou are able to resist 6 internal enemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages (ashta =\r\npashas) or not. If your ability to resist them is increasing, you are makin=\r\ng progress. EVEN IF your Kundalini is fast asleep, you are still making pro=\r\ngress. When you completely overcome them, Kundalini (your self-awareness) w=\r\nill automatically ascend to the top and meet Her Lord (true Self).\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;One word on surrendering to a personal dei=\r\nty. Though true surrender is helpful, most people do not have it. They simp=\r