a=\r\nt *lightness of conditioning* is the most important thing. One with dense c=\r\nonditioning will find SOME way to fail even if a great guru or god are read=\r\ny to help. &nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * &nbsp; Now, the question is: How do we red=\r\nuce our conditioning? Unfortunately, there is no single magic bullet. Think=\r\ning of a god, mantras, bhajans, japam, homam etc can help, but they need to=\r\n be augmented by regular introspection and self-improvement. &nbsp; Taking =\r\nmind away from its current pre-occupations (e.g. &quot;I am smart&quot;, &quot;I am doing =\r\ngood sadhana&quot;, &quot;I am mad at X&quot;, &quot;I did not get what I deserve in Y&quot;, &quot;I am =\r\nbetter than X&quot;, &quot;I must have Y at any cost&quot; etc etc) is key to eventually o=\r\nvercoming conditioning,\n for these thoughts keep *reinforcing* the conditio=\r\nning! &nbsp; To reduce the regular pre-occupations of mind, different image=\r\nry/visualization may work better for some people. &nbsp; One approach is to=\r\n contemplate god whenever possible, in the middle of any activity. You can =\r\nimagine a being in your mind, either as an ideal/able person or as a princi=\r\nple/ideal/ability that exists in many beings, that is so perfect and fascin=\r\nating for the mind to contemplate that it does not care about other objects=\r\n around that are making shadripus and ashtapashas work on the mind. Wheneve=\r\nr mind is about to entertain its regular debilitating pre-occupations, one =\r\ncan try to contemplate god instead. &nbsp; Mind is a wild animal. As Pi say=\r\ns in the movie &quot;Life of Pi&quot; about the tiger on the boat, wild animals can&#39;t=\r\n be transformed or domesticated, but they can be trained into some habits! =\r\n&nbsp; Whenever one is enjoying a sensual pleasure, if one\n thinks &quot;the omn=\r\nipresent God is enjoying this thru this instrument&quot; and starts contemplatin=\r\ng the qualities of that god instead of thinking too much about limited sens=\r\ne objects, one is better placed to reduce the damage done by shadripus. Whe=\r\nnever one is angry at someone for what they did, if one thinks &quot;the omnipre=\r\nsent God is giving me the fruits of my karmas thru that instrument&quot; and sta=\r\nrts contemplating the qualities of that god instead of being angry at someo=\r\nne, one is better placed to reduce the damage done by shadripus. And so on.=\r\n &nbsp; In the beginning, even contemplation of god becomes laced with ego.=\r\n Every now and then, the activity ends up becoming about oneself rather tha=\r\nn about god (&quot;*I* am doing this nice bhajan&quot;, &quot;*I* am doing this nice homam=\r\n&quot;, &quot;I think *I* am making progress through this&quot;). With effort and persever=\r\nance, one can avoid making it about oneself and keep it centered on the sup=\r\nreme power that runs the show. Just as it\n takes a long time to train a wil=\r\nd animal, it takes a long time to train mind! &nbsp; Try to develop devotio=\r\nn and surrender. Based on all that you read and heard, develop of a concept=\r\n/principle of god that is so superb and fascinarting. Visualize/contemplate=\r\n that concept as frequently as possible, especially when meditating. When m=\r\nind veers off into other things, gently steer it back. Don&#39;t spend too much=\r\n time dissecting what mind is doing and why. Just put it back gently into c=\r\nontemplating god. Try to make it about god rather than about yourself. &nbs=\r\np; The main drawback of the sadhana of most people is that they make it abo=\r\nut themselves at some level or the other. Though that is unavoidable, try t=\r\no break free from it. &nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * &nbsp; Finally, one can try to =\r\novercome the limited sense of self and engage in selfless actions that bene=\r\nfit\n a larger set of people than oneself. What stops us from truly loving g=\r\nod is our deep and sub-conscious love for *ourselves* (i.e. our *limited* n=\r\notion of self that drives the current body-mind complex). One way to overco=\r\nme that is to selflessly love others. After all, other people around us are=\r\n as much replicas of god as we are. If we cannot empathize with them, love =\r\nthem and give them unconditionally, how can we ever hope to transcend the l=\r\nimited sense of Self and truly love omnipresent God? &nbsp; \n&lt;div style=3D&quot;=\r\nBACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYLE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:arial, helvetica=\r\n, clean, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);FONT-SIZE:13px;&quot;&gt;Best regards, Narasim=\r\nha -------- Astrology &amp; Spirituality Resources: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; tar=\r\nget=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://www.vedicastrologer.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.vedicast=\r\nrologer.org/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;BACKGROUND-COLOR:transparent;FONT-STYL=\r\nE:normal;FONT-FAMILY:arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif;COLOR:rgb(0,0,0);F=\r\nONT-SIZE:13px;&quot;&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div&gt;\n&lt;blockquote style=3D&quot;BORDER-=\r\nLEFT:rgb(16,16,255) 2px solid;&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;FONT-FAMILY:arial, helvetica=\r\n, sans-serif;FONT-SIZE:10pt;&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;FONT-FAMILY:times new roman, n=\r\new york, times, serif;FONT-SIZE:12pt;&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=3D&quot;Aria=\r\nl&quot; size=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;\n&lt;div style=3D&quot;BORDER-BOTTOM:#ccc 1px solid;BORDER-LEFT:#ccc =\r\n1px solid;HEIGHT:0px;FONT-SIZE:0px;BORDER-TOP:#ccc 1px solid;BORDER-RIGHT:#=\r\nccc 1px solid;&quot; class=3D&quot;yiv255306719hr&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGH=\r\nT:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; Leela Sastry &lt;leela.sastry@...&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b=\r\n&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;FONT-WEIGHT:bold;&quot;&gt;To:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&